    "content": "Web search results for query: \"Claude Code remote development SSH VSCode tunnel 2025\"\n\nI'll search for information about Claude Code remote development with SSH VSCode tunnel in 2025.\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Control Claude Code Remotely with Zero-Friction SSH Tunnels\",\"url\":\"https://compiledthoughts.pages.dev/blog/claude-code-remote-ssh-tunnel/\"},{\"title\":\"VSCode Remote Development via SSH and Tunnel – FASRC DOCS\",\"url\":\"https://docs.rc.fas.harvard.edu/kb/vscode-remote-development-via-ssh-or-tunnel/\"},{\"title\":\"Developing with Remote Tunnels\",\"url\":\"https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/remote/tunnels\"},{\"title\":\"Remote Development using SSH\",\"url\":\"https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/remote/ssh\"},{\"title\":\"Switching to Claude Code and VSCode Inside Docker | Hacker News\",\"url\":\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=44533044\"},{\"title\":\"Switching to Claude Code + VSCode inside Docker\",\"url\":\"https://timsh.org/claude-inside-docker/\"},{\"title\":\"Claude Code overview - Anthropic\",\"url\":\"https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/claude-code/overview\"},{\"title\":\"Remote Development FAQ\",\"url\":\"https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/remote/faq\"},{\"title\":\"Claude 4: Opus vs Sonnet, Benchmarks, and Dev Workflow with Claude Code - DEV Community\",\"url\":\"https://dev.to/nodeshiftcloud/claude-4-opus-vs-sonnet-benchmarks-and-dev-workflow-with-claude-code-11fa\"},{\"title\":\"How to Integrate Claude Code with VSCode and JetBrains?\",\"url\":\"https://apidog.com/blog/claude-code-ide-integrations/\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about Claude Code remote development with SSH VSCode tunnel in 2025:\n\n## Claude Code Remote Development Overview\n\nClaude Code can be set up with passwordless SSH tunnels to control it on remote machines, eliminating authentication friction and streamlining your AI-powered development workflow. The solution involves a properly configured SSH tunnel with passwordless authentication and smart aliases.\n\n## Key Features and Setup\n\n### SSH Tunnel Configuration\nYou can create an SSH tunnel alias for remote access like: `alias claude-remote='ssh -q -o LogLevel=quiet -L 8082:localhost:8080 username@remote-ip -t \"claude --dangerously-skip-permissions; bash\"'`. This provides one command access with no passwords, no manual port forwarding, just instant access to Claude Code running on your remote machine.\n\n### VSCode Remote Tunnels\nThe VSCode Remote Tunnels extension provides multiple approaches for remote development:\n\n1. **Remote Tunnels via CLI**: The Visual Studio Code Remote - Tunnels extension lets you connect to a remote machine, like a desktop PC or virtual machine (VM), via a secure tunnel without the requirement of SSH. The code CLI command downloads and starts the VS Code Server on the machine and then creates a tunnel to it.\n\n2. **SSH-based Remote Development**: You can develop on remote machines or VMs using Visual Studio Code Remote Development and SSH. All communication between the server and the VS Code client is accomplished through the authenticated, secure SSH tunnel.\n\n## Claude Code Specific Features (2025)\n\nClaude Code is Anthropic's agentic coding tool that lives in your terminal and helps you turn ideas into code faster than ever before. Key capabilities include:\n\n- Works in your terminal: Not another chat window. Not another IDE. Claude Code meets you where you already work, with the tools you already love\n- Claude Code can directly edit files, run commands, and create commits\n- Claude Code is composable and scriptable. `tail -f app.log | claude -p \"Slack me if you see any anomalies appear in this log stream\"` works\n\n## Integration with VSCode\n\nInstall the Claude Code extension via VSCode Extensions, enable features using Cmd+Esc (Mac) or Ctrl+Esc (Windows/Linux) to open Claude Code directly. The extension shares open files, diagnostics (lint errors, warnings), and selections with Claude Code.\n\n## Docker-based Isolation\n\nSome developers are switching to running Claude Code in an isolated Docker environment using VSCode's Dev Container feature. Since the container has isolated environment, Claude doesn't have any access to your local secrets (like your SSH key) and won't be able to use any external integrations without you knowing.\n\n## Recent Developments (2025)\n\nIn 2025, Anthropic unveiled Claude Opus 4 and Claude Sonnet 4. Claude Opus 4 stands out as the most advanced model for developers, consistently delivering top-tier results on long, uninterrupted workflows with a commanding 72.5% on SWE-bench and 43.2% on Terminal-bench.\n\nThe combination of Claude Code with VSCode's remote development capabilities provides a powerful workflow for developers in 2025, offering both SSH-based and tunnel-based approaches for seamless remote development with AI assistance."
