updates were in December 2024, making these recommendations current for 2025.\n\n**Todoist** stands out as the world's favorite task manager and to-do list app, trusted by 30 million people and teams. Todoist reminders used to be a paid subscription part of the app but many people complained about this a lot and it is now for all free users, with no limits. As a cross-platform app, Todoist is free allowing you to use it anywhere and reminders too. It features easy-flowing, natural language capture and allows you to quickly, using natural language, to tag a task with a reminder and using a phrase like \"!30m\" get notified in 30 minutes. It is one of the reasons why people have moved to Todoist for quick task capture.\n\n**Microsoft To-Do** (formerly Wunderlist) offers reminder abilities and is basic, easy to use and good for those already baked into apps like Microsoft Outlook that can flag emails already as tasks in Microsoft To-Do. The Samsung reminder app can sync with To Do on personal Microsoft accounts as well as work and school accounts.\n\n### Apple Ecosystem Excellence\n\nFor Apple users, **Things 3** is highlighted as exceptional. It combines functionality and beauty with features like a system-wide tool for quickly adding tasks, integration with your calendar so you can see your appointments while planning your day, intuitive keyboard shortcuts, reminders with native notifications, and syncing to an iPhone and iPad app. Things 3 is one of the best looking reminder & to-do list apps ever. Adored by millions, Things 3 is a minimal and beautiful to-do list app with the reminder features for making sure you never forget anything.\n\nApple's built-in **Reminders** app has also significantly improved. Reminders has gone from being a very basic to-do list to a solid task management app. It has tags, due dates, sub-tasks, and Smart Lists, you can share tasks and lists with other Apple users, and you can even trigger reminders based on your location. In the latest